{
  "title": "Benchmarking REST APIs with FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides an overview of how to utilize FastAPI for benchmarking the performance of REST APIs within Python 3.12+ ecosystem.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is a modern, high-performance web framework for building APIs in Python.",
    "It includes built-in support for benchmarking API endpoints using tools like Blackfire and Pyperf.",
    "You'll learn how to leverage these tools to measure the performance of your FastAPI application.",
    "This guide assumes familiarity with Python 3.12+, FastAPI, and REST APIs."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/healthcheck')\ndef healthcheck():\n    return {'status': 'OK'}\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    app.run(host='127.0.0.1', port=8000)"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi.testclient import TestClient\nfrom blackfire import new_client\n\napp = FastAPI()\nclient = new_client(project_id='YOUR_BLACKFIRE_PROJECT_ID')\n\n@app.get('/benchmark')\ndef benchmark():\n    # Your API endpoint logic here\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    client.start_profiler()\n    with TestClient(app) as test_client:\n        response = test_client.get('/benchmark')\n        assert response.status_code == 200\n    client.stop_and_upload()"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "FastAPI version: latest (v0.70.0 as of writing this example)",
    "Python version: 3.12+",
    "Blackfire: Ensure you have Blackfire installed and a valid project ID for profiling."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Profiling with Blackfire requires additional setup and may impact the performance of your application.",
    "While Pyperf is included in Python's standard library, it may not be as accurate or user-friendly as some specialized benchmarking tools.",
    "Always consider real-world testing and monitoring to validate your API's performance."
  ]
}
